Apodeme that is part of an adult.

Apodeme that facilitates rotation of haustellum relative to the rostrum (McKellar et al., 2020). One (ventroposterior) arm is attached to the external cuticle of the rostrum, continuous with the lacinia (Grimaldi, 1994; McKellar et al., 2020). An anterior arm is continuous with the external cuticle of the haustellum (McKellar et al., 2020). A dorsal arm is free and forms the insertion site for proboscis muscle 4 (McKellar et al., 2020). This muscle is also attached to a rigid part of the rostrum, so that it rotates the apodeme and extends that haustellum as it contracts (McKellar et al., 2020).
Long, slender apodeme extending from the base of the phallus into the body.
Muscle cell of a visceral muscle of the adult.
Muscle cell of a longitudinal muscle of the adult. These muscles surrounds the intestinal tract and ducts of the reproductive system, together with a layer of circular muscle.
Muscle cell of a circular muscle of the adult. These muscles surround some internal organs such as the intestinal tract and ducts of the reproductive system.
Muscle cell of the visceral muscle of the adult esophagus.

Muscle cell of the circular muscle of the adult esophagus. There is a single layer of circular muscles forming bands 4-6um wide and 3um thick. The fiber muscles at the anterior end of the esophagus, near the cibarium, are 6-7.5um thick.
Cell that is part of the circumferential muscle fibers that forms a narrow band around the esophagus, at the anterior end of the cardia.

Cell that is part of the circular muscle fibers of the adult crop. In the stalk, it consists of wide bands 1.5um thick and 3-7um wide. In the sac, thick muscle fibers extend around the base of each lobe, converging posteriorly, and the distended portions of the wall are covered with a plexus of branched and interlacing fibers 1-3um thick.

Cell that is part of the thin scattering of muscle fibers that covers the outer layer of the adult proventriculus (cardia). It is one cell thick, except at the anterior end of the proventriculus, where the muscle of the outer layer meets the muscle of the esophagus.
Muscle cell of a muscle of the adult midgut, surrounding the epithelium (Miller, 1950).
Muscle cell of the circular muscle of the adult midgut. Circular muscles are surrounded by the outer longitudinal fibers.
Muscle cell of the longitudinal muscle of the adult midgut. The longitudinal fibers surround the circular muscle fibers.
Cell that are part of the muscle fibers of the hindgut, the posterior part of the alimentary canal. It contains longitudinal and circular muscle fibers.

label.value: adult posterior hindgut circular muscle cell

value.value: Muscle cell of the circular muscle of the adult posterior hindgut, located as an outside layer to the inner longitudinal fibers. It is a single layer of thick, closely set circular fibers. Muscular fibers are 3um thick and 10um wide in the rectal sac, and 3-5um thick in the posterior rectum.

label.value: adult posterior hindgut longitudinal muscle cell

value.value: Muscle cell of the longitudinal muscle of the adult posterior hindgut, located as an inside layer to the outer circular fibers. Longitudinal fibers are 3-5um wide and 1um thick.

label.value: adult salivary gland suspensor muscle cell

value.value: Muscle cell of the muscle that extends from the anterior end of the salivary gland to the cardia. (Miller, 1950 pg 440-1, 451).
Muscle cell of a muscle of the adult that is associated with the heart.

Fine fibril that is found in a meshwork layer between the outer ventral longitudinal muscle layer and the circular muscle layer of the adult heart. The fibrils run parallel to the longitudinal axis of the heart and are crosslinked by elements of a similar nature.
Muscle cell of a bilateral adult heart muscle that is involved in modulation of the flow of hemolymph into the cardiac tube, and support of the dorsal vessel during locomotion.

definition.value: Activity of this muscle causes the penis to be protruded (Ferris, 1950).

value.value: Muscle cell that is part of a striated array of circular muscle fibers forming an almost continuous sheet around the common oviduct (Miller, 1950; McQueen et al., 2022).
Circular muscle cell that is part of the thick muscle layer that surrounds the uterus (Miller, 1950; Middleton et al., 2006; McQueen et al., 2022).
Muscle cell that is part of the spermathecal duct. These longitudinal muscle fibers stretch the entire length of the duct (Avila et al., 2012).

definition.value: There are no circular muscle fibers in the spermathecal duct (Avila et al., 2012).

value.value: Muscle cell of a muscle that is part of an adult gonadal sheath.

Muscle cell of a muscle that is part of the adult ovarian sheath. This is found in the median layer of the sheath, with discontinuous circular muscle found closest to the ovariole and occasional longitudinal fibers in the outer part of the median layer of the sheath (Cummings, 1973).
Muscle cell of a muscle that is part of the adult testis sheath.
